I&#39;ve fixed the issue! Guess what? it wasn&#39;t related to the SpaceShip itself, but with the way they are generated!

    enemyAdder = Observable.Interval(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(3)).Subscribe(_ =&gt; this.Add(new Ship()
                {
                    Top = Utils.Random.Next((int) Constants.GroundTop),
                    Left = width, 
                }));

this subscription generated space ships every 3 seconds, but for some reason, I forgot the `ObserveOn` part.

This is the fixed version:

    enemyAdder = Observable.Interval(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(3)).ObserveOn(Dispatcher.CurrentDispatcher).Subscribe(_ =&gt; this.Add(new Ship()
                {
                    Top = Utils.Random.Next((int) Constants.GroundTop),
                    Left = width, 
                }));

With the ObserveOn, it works! I wonder why it worked without it. Maybe I was just lucky.

